---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'About | burninjurycalc.com';
const description = 'About burninjurycalc.com: our mission, the editorial team, and what we do and don\'t do.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>About</h1>

  <p>burninjurycalc.com is a free informational resource about burn injury compensation, reconstructive surgery, life-care planning, and the legal framework governing burn-injury cases in the United States. The site exists to help patients, families, and other interested parties understand the rough scope of compensation that burn cases produce &mdash; with enough specificity to inform initial decisions, while staying honest about the limits of general informational content.</p>

  <h2>What we do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide a calculator that estimates recovery ranges based on burn depth, Total Body Surface Area (TBSA), cause, body location, age, income, and jurisdiction, using published settlement data and standard damages frameworks.</li>
    <li>Explain how burn-injury cases are valued: damages categories (including disfigurement as a separate category in most states), reconstructive-surgery cost projection, life-care planning, and the role of insurance and defendant assets.</li>
    <li>Document burn classification (depth and TBSA), the Lund-Browder chart, and the prognosis information that drives both medical care and legal compensation.</li>
    <li>Provide step-by-step guidance for what to do after a burn injury &mdash; verified burn-center care, evidence preservation, attorney consultation, and insurance coordination.</li>
    <li>Address common misconceptions about burn-injury claims.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Provide legal advice. We are not attorneys.</li>
    <li>Provide medical advice. We are not medical providers.</li>
    <li>Review individual cases or predict outcomes.</li>
    <li>Refer to or accept compensation from specific law firms.</li>
    <li>Collect personal information beyond standard analytics.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The team</h2>
  <p>The editorial team is a small group of burn-injury paralegals and life-care planning specialists at The Click Lab. Detailed bios at <a href="/editorial">the editorial team page</a>.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Editorial questions, corrections, or interview requests: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.</p>
</BaseLayout>
